 3.","type":"text"}],"role":"assistant"},"context":{"branch":"main","cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","head":"33f522b9832b7de0b78d5f52e9cbb125d3f2403c","repo":"git@github.com:evintunador/conversation-ledger.git"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:48648da3-5c2c-4827-96d5-7a6ed13224df","seq":336},"id":"ev1-444f59a1c5864f5ac1e1cac7f506847413a9768c1443036d8e473c533967a1c9","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-20T23:12:51.638Z","producer":{"session_id":"48648da3-5c2c-4827-96d5-7a6ed13224df","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.7.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","effort":"high","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"text":"## Deliverable 2 done ✅ — committed as `33f522b` (0.7.0)\n\n**What shipped:** the opt-in \"remember confirmed secrets\" feature, exactly as we scoped it.\n\n- **Off by default.** With no config, the store is never read or created. Turn it on with `{\"redact\": {\"knownSecrets\": true}}` in `.cledger.json` or global config.\n- **Write path:** `cledger redact <id> --pattern <regex>` now remembers the exact value(s) it scrubbed. `--all` (whole-content blanking) remembers nothing, and values under 8 chars are dropped so common short strings can't over-match later.\n- **Read path:** once on, capture-time redaction exact-matches every remembered value out of new events, recorded under a distinct `known-secret` rule id (kept separate from env masking in the audit trail).\n- **Storage:** `.git/conversation-ledger/known-secrets.json`, right beside the allowlist. It holds plaintext (a fingerprint is a one-way hash — can't drive exact-match scrubbing), but `.git/` is never tracked or pushed by git, so it's structurally local and unshared — satisfying your \"git always ignores it\" condition.\n\n**Verification:** 7 new tests (unit store behavior, on/off gating, min-length guard, `--all` no-op, `.git/` location) + 